==Latin==
===Suffix===
'''-ī'''
#(''nominative and vocative plural masculine ending for [[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin second declension|second declension]] nouns'')
#(''genitive singular ending for second declension nouns'')
#(''vocative singular masculine ending for second declension nouns ending in [[-ius]]'')
#(''dative singular ending for [[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin third declension|third declension]] nouns'')
#(''ablative singular ending for third declension i-stem nouns, such as [[rete]], [[animal]] and sometimes [[navis]]'')
#(''perfect active indicative first-person singular ending for verbs'')
#(''present passive infinitive ending for [[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin third conjugation|third conjugation]] verbs'')

==Turkish==
===Suffix===
'''-ı''' (''with back vowel harmony'')

'''-i''' (''with front vowel harmony'')

Other forms: -u, -ü (if last vocal is o,ö,u or ü), -yı, -yi, -yu, -yü (after a vocal), -nı, -ni, -nu, -nü (after possessive)

Examples:
ev-i, araba-yı, yol-u, babası-nı

